summary: Old Art, Circa 2016 Following yesterday’s concept art of the hunky Sir Tristan, today we’ve got Princess Ysette in a variety of...
caption:
Old Art, Circa 2016

Following yesterday’s concept art of the hunky Sir Tristan, today we’ve got Princess Ysette in a variety of dresses. And I hate all of them.

Well… they’re alright, but at the time I was really struggling with Ysette’s character. Dresses? Make up? All foreign stuff to me, and I got frustrated that with Tristan I had a strong idea of how to draw sabatons and tassets, but when it came to Ysette, I could only shrug and draw ‘a dress’. And at the time I didn’t move past the idea of princess = dress, or that I didn’t need a girl in a dress to contrast with having a girl in armour.

Anyways, maybe some of you will enjoy these drawings, maybe you agree with me. If you’re curious to see how I ended up solving Ysette’s outfit issue (and pushing her character even further in general), stay tuned.

blog.name: surferofrowdybliss
blog.title: Visual Play
blog.description:
Deborah Coulter

Scissors in hand, I make collages exploring the freedom and fun of visual play. I get lost in the joy of selecting, cutting, and rearranging images. The process begins as I discover the infinite possibilities life offers through the spaciousness of an open heart. Children, animals, and nature lead the way.

I invite you to join me in these adventures of scissors & glue blending with imagination in the exquisite present.
